Instruction: With the battery inserted and all switches ON, use a multimeter referenced to PSU negative to measure the voltage on the presumed +12 V conductor at the input and output of each control module in sequence (CM1 in+, CM1 out+, CM2 in+, CM2 out+, … CM8 out+). In each case also confirm the corresponding 0 V line continuity. This will locate where along the series chain the +12 V (and/or 0 V) line is lost or miswired between CM1 and the load module.
