2026-04-21 01:35:17 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Input Cable (+) 3', 'Control Switch 3'] hypothesis_explanation="Measurements show +12 V present at Control Module 3 input+, but both switch terminals and output+ are at 0 V while the switch itself has good continuity across its contacts. The diagnostic tool reports that cable 'Control Input Cable (+) 3' has a disconnected end (its internal port ‘n’ is floating and no longer attached to Control Switch 3 as per design). This indicates an open circuit between the internal termination of Control Input Cable (+) 3 and the input side of Control Switch 3 (e.g., broken solder joint, fractured trace, or mis‑connection). As a result, +12 V never reaches the switch or the module’s output, and the series chain is interrupted from CM3 onward, explaining the absence of voltage at CM3 out+ and all downstream modules and the load. Repairing/reconnecting the internal joint between Control Input Cable (+) 3 and Control Switch 3 (or replacing CM3 to restore that connection) should restore the +12 V path to the remaining modules and allow the lamp to operate, assuming no additional faults."
